==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|pece|pece, peas, pees|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|pais||peace|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|pax|pāx|peace|lang=la}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|paḱ-|to fasten, stick, place|lang=en}}, related to Latin {{term|paciscor|pacīscor|agree, stipulate|lang=la}}, Latin {{term|pango|pangō|fasten, fix|lang=la}}; see [[pact]]. Displaced native [[Middle English]] {{term|frith|lang=enm}}, {{term|frede|lang=enm}} "peace" (from [[Old English]] {{term|friþ||lang=ang}}, {{term|freod|frēod|peace|lang=ang}}), Middle English {{term|sib|sib, sibbe|peace|lang=enm}} (from Old English {{term|sibb||peace, kinship|lang=ang}}), Middle English {{term|grith||peace, security|lang=enm}} (from [[Old English]] {{term|griþ||lang=ang}} and Old Norse {{term|grið||lang=non}}), Middle English {{term|saught|saht, saught|peace, reconciliation|lang=enm}} (from Old English {{term|seht||lang=ang}}, {{term|sæht||peace, pact, agreement|lang=ang}}).

